body:
## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

wb.xlsx.writeFile is very very very slow.

Lib version: 4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce


```javascript
    console.time('xlsx');
    const rows: any[] = [];
    const keys: string[] = [];
    for (let i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
      keys.push(Math.random() + '');
    }
    for (let i = 0; i < 5e5 /* 500k */; i++) {
      rows.push(Object.fromEntries(keys.map((k) => [k, Math.random() + ''])));
    }
    console.timeLog('xlsx', 'load', rows.length);
    const testXlsx = async () => {
      const book = XLSX.utils.book_new();
      const sheet = XLSX.utils.json_to_sheet(rows, { dense: true });
      XLSX.utils.book_append_sheet(book, sheet);
      console.timeLog('xlsx', 'xlsx insert rows', sheet['!ref']);
      const buf = XLSX.writeXLSX(book, { type: 'buffer', compression: true, WTF: true });
      await fs.writeFile('temp/test-xlsx.xlsx', buf);
      console.timeLog('xlsx', 'xlsx write');
    };
    const testExcel = async () => {
      const book = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
      const sheet = book.addWorksheet('data');
      sheet.addRows([keys].concat(rows.map((e) => keys.map((c) => mustStr(e[c])))));
      console.timeLog('xlsx', 'exceljs insert rows', sheet.rowCount);
      await book.xlsx.writeFile('temp/test-excel.xlsx', {
        useStyles: false,
        useSharedStrings: false,
        zip: { compression: 'DEFLATE', compressionOptions: { level: 6 } },
      });
      console.timeLog('xlsx', 'exceljs write');
    };

    await testXlsx();
    await testExcel();
```

This code compares `xlsx` and `exceljs`, when I execute the code, the `xlsx` part will output as expected, but `exceljs` part cannot. The output looks like this:

```bash
xlsx: 1.781s load 500000
xlsx: 2.354s xlsx insert rows A1:T500001
xlsx: 17.726s xlsx write
xlsx: 20.088s exceljs insert rows 500001
^C%
Time: 0h:01m:37s
```

## The expected behaviour:

Should write to file successfully.
